==Introduction==
The '''Reference''' widget '''displays a list of pages''' from a specific Source Concept with specific Property referring to the current page.

The "Reference" widget might be placed along other Concept properties and widgets, thus allowing to display the list in any place on the page.
The widget is displayed on View and Edit pages.
The widget allows to apply different styles to rendered list.

It supports similar functionality to the [[Help:Related Data|Related Data]] widget.
Both of them display the list(s) of pages referring to the current page.
The '''Related Data''' widget creates a separate "Related Information" section at the bottom of the page where it '''displays MULTIPLE tabs with separate lists''' for different referring Source Concepts.
The "Reference" widget on the other hand '''displays only ONE specific list''' (one of the lists displayed in "Related Data" section).
The list displayed using "Reference" widget is removed from the "Related Data" tabs.



==Definition==
<pre>
<concept name="{SOURCE}">
  <structure>
    <property name="Property 1"/>
    <property name="Property 2"/>
    <property name="Property 3"/>
    <property name="{REFERRING PROPERTY NAME}" refersTo="{TARGET}"/>
  </structure>
</concept>

<concept name="{TARGET}">
  <structure>
    <property name="Property A"/>
    <property name="Property B"/>
    <reference name="{REFERENCE NAME}" refersFrom="{SOURCE}" subobject="{SUBOBJECT}"
               property="{REFERRING PROPERTY NAME}" filter="{FILTER}"
               sortBy="{SORT PROPERTY}" sortOrder="{SORT ORDER}"
               context="{CONTEXT}" label="{LABEL}" format="{FORMAT}" icon="{ICON}">
      <columns>
        <column name="{COLUMN NAME}"/>
        <column name="{COLUMN NAME}"/>
        <column name="{COLUMN NAME}"/>
      </columns>
    </reference>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {SOURCE}
| A name of the Source Concept.
|-
! {SUBOBJECT}
| A name of the Subobject of Source Concept, which holds the {REFERRING PROPERTY NAME} Property. (Applicable only if the Property is a part of Subobject instead of Concept)
|-
! {TARGET}
| A name of the Target Concept.
|-
! {REFERRING PROPERTY NAME}
| A name of the property of 'Page' type in the Source Concept which refers to the Target Concept.
|-
! {REFERENCE NAME}
| A name of the Reference.
|-
! {LABEL}
| A label of the Reference, if not set the {REFERENCE NAME} is used as a label.
|-
! {FILTER}
| An additional filter to be set on the related entities (e.g. [[Test result:Limited success]] to limit the Test Cases to be displayed only to Limited Success)
|-
! {SORT PROPERTY}
| The name of the property to be used for sorting purposes
|-
! {SORT ORDER}
| The order of the sorting. The following values are allowed:
* ''desc''
* ''asc''
|-
! {CONTEXT}
| By default all records displayed by Reference Widget are related to the current page (link to current page).
Sometimes it is required to change that context, e.g. on Exercise Working Group page to display records related to Exercise instead.
The {CONTEXT} option allows to change context by defining a name of property on the current page which represents a new context. ("Is part of" to point to Exercise)
|-
! {FORMAT}
| A layout type used to render referring Source Concept pages. The following options are allowed:
* table. The "table" layout displays a table with referring pages. The first column displays a Source page name, and the following columns display the values of the properties defined in the {COLUMNS} attribute.
* list. The "link" layout displays a list of referring pages. The main list heading displays a Source page name, and under it the values of the properties defined in the {COLUMNS} attribute.
* link. The "link" layout displays simple list of links to the referring Source pages.
* gallery. The "gallery" layout displays gallery of images/logos associated with the pages.
* gallerylist. The "gallerylist" layout displays a list of images/logos associated with the pages with the values of the properties defined in the {COLUMNS} attribute..
|-
! {COLUMN NAME}
| A name of the column to be displayed next to the page name.
|-
! {ICON}
| An optional icon (with link) to be displayed instead of a page name. Useful for cases where page name might be long and might not be user friendly (e.g. with automatically generated numbering)
|}



==Example==
<pre>
<concept name="Capability Configuration" ...>          <!-- Source Concept -->
  <structure>
    <property name="Title"/>
    <property name="Description"/>
    <property name="Is hosted on"/>
    <property name="Is lead by" refersTo="User">       <!-- Referring Page Property -->
  </structure>
</concept>

<concept name="User" ...>                              <!-- Target Concept -->
  <structure>
    <property name="First name"/>
    <property name="Last name"/>
    <property name="Organization"/>
    <property name="Function"/>
    <reference name="Capabilities" refersFrom="Capability Configuration" property="Is lead by" format="table">
      <columns>
        <column name="Title"/>
        <column name="Description"/>
        <column name="Is hosted on"/>
      </columns>
    </reference>
  </structure>
</concept>
</pre>


==User Interface==
The "Reference" widget is displayed on View and Edit Pages of the Target Concept ("User" in the example above).

